<br>
I hunt for exp and that damn jawbone... Which still may or may not drop...  <br>
<br>
I'm sorry, I think the front 4 golems in the front of the temple as a camp...  Well, rather i ask if you won't pull it if I'm quading them...  I've been working a LONG time...  trying to get the jawbone...  I'm not a loot hoard...  I find myself the only one in the zone at times.. and if named spawn...  I'm gonna kill it...  But if it is crowded, I try to be helpful and more then willing to share...  Even if I track a named... if I know that area of the temple is camped.. I won't try to sneak a pull...    Some will even note I pulled it for them so they are sure to get it...  Once I lost my temper, cause after hours of camping hte front golems.. somebody came and broke it up...  <br>
<br>
I understand ppl saying it's a FFA zone... but come on now...  If you just came into the zone.. and a named pop or is up...  It should be belong to the ppl that's been working on clearing the area...   How would you feel if that happen to you?  <br>
<br>
Once I got trained while killing heirophant named...   After taking some effort to root the train.. so I can kill it...   I was KSed...   Rather just giving me the item...  he offered to random it... How very big of him, no?  Sheesh...  If he wanted it that badly, it was all his...  Let it be...  I'm quite sure he didn't train me...  ACtually i'm sure of it...  What annoyed me was he offered to random for it, when he ksed my pull...  Mind you.. I was at 80% hp and 55% mana even after rooting the train away...  and was less then 50 when the train hit me...  I could have killed it on my own easily...    But off the topic...  <br>
<br>
Saying a zone is FFA doesn't give you the right to be a jerk...  Sorry, that's the best way to put it...  Yes, maybe there is no &quot;camp&quot;  but if a group is at the back of the temple...  Assume the little shissar ruins there is for them...   if a group is camping the south side..  assume the mob on the south side are theirs...  It might not be a standred camp... But send a friendly tell, &quot;can I pull this?&quot;, &quot;Are these yours?&quot;, &quot;Mind if I take one of those golems/shissar?&quot;, &quot;Are you on the named?&quot; I try my best to be nice...  I'm sure there are cases ppl can say where it didn't seems like it...  Hopefully it's not what ppl think of me...  I presonally like the grey...  It's been good to me...  =D  <br>
<br>
